data.title: Correct Process Participants
data.description: You correctly identified the two participants in the process: the 'Loan Applicant' and the 'Credit Institute'. Good job!

data.title: Incorrect Participant Names
data.description: The names of the participants are incorrect. They should be 'Loan Applicant' and 'Credit Institute', not 'Car Buyer' and 'Car Manufacturer'. Please correct this.

data.title: Correct Process Flow
data.description: The process flow is mostly correct, but there are some errors. For example, the 'Send credit request' task should only have one outgoing flow, not two. Also, the 'Review quote' task should not have an outgoing flow to the 'End Event'. Please correct these errors.

data.title: Correct Use of Gateways
data.description: You correctly used the 'Exclusive Gateway' and 'Parallel Gateway' in the 'Credit Institute' process. However, the 'Parallel Gateway' in the 'Loan Applicant' process is not necessary. Please remove it.

data.title: Correct Use of Events
data.description: You correctly used the 'Start Event' and 'End Event' in both processes. However, the 'Intermediate Catch Event' in the 'Loan Applicant' process should not have an outgoing flow to the 'Send credit request' task. Please correct this.

data.title: Correct Use of Tasks
data.description: You correctly used tasks in both processes. However, the 'Send quote' task should not have an outgoing flow to the 'End Event'. Please correct this.

data.title: Correct Use of Message Flows
data.description: You correctly used message flows between the two processes. However, the 'Send credit request' task should not have a message flow to the 'Credit request received' start event. Please correct this.

data.title: Correct Use of Sequence Flows
data.description: You correctly used sequence flows in both processes. However, some of the flows are incorrect. For example, the 'Send credit request' task should not have a sequence flow to the 'Quote received' intermediate catch event. Please correct these errors.
